# Session end — memory checklist

When the user ends a session, mentions handoff/distill, or you see `[agent-memory] Session end` in context:

## 1. Read hook log (if exists)

```text
~/.cursor/hooks/agent-memory-session.log
```

Last lines contain the sessionEnd checklist (also in stderr during hook run).

## 2. Execute checklist

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| Handoff | Only if `$MEMORY_HOME/config.json` → `handoff_mode` is not `off` — update `<repo>/AGENT_HANDOFF.md` when phase/next step changed |
| Distill | Hooks auto-distill on sessionEnd; review `merge-staging/`; curate Decisions from staging |
| Fallback | If distill lacks detail → open chat link `[title](uuid)` in `chats/projects/<slug>.md` ## Recent |
| Verify | `verify-memory.py --memory-home $MEMORY_HOME` |
| Pending | `list-chats.py --pending` — note unprocessed chats |

## 3. Semantic merge (not optional for new distill)

- `--apply` only updates **Recent** — never replaces agent curation of `## Decisions`
- Use skill **semantic-merge** + `templates/chats/semantic-merge-prompt.md`

## Paths

- Framework: `$FRAMEWORK_ROOT` from `~/.cursor/hooks/agent-memory.env` (set by `install-memory-hooks.sh`)
- Hub: `$MEMORY_HOME` from `~/.cursor/hooks/agent-memory.env` or `<install>/memory/config.json`
- Edit log: `~/.cursor/hooks/agent-memory-edit.log` (afterFileEdit saves)

Install hooks: `bash scripts/install-memory-hooks.sh` (from your framework clone)
